'''Agnes Mundia Limbo''' (born 12 May 1957 in [[Kanginzila]], [[Zambezi Region]]) is a [[Namibia]]n politician. A member of the [[Rally for Democracy and Progress (Namibia)|Rally for Democracy and Progress]] (RDP), she was named the Deputy Secretary of the party at their founding conference in December 2008. She was elected to the [[National Assembly of Namibia]] with RDP in the [[Namibian general election, 2009|2009 general election]].
==Career== Limbo was a member of [[SWAPO]] from an early encounter with SWAPO exile leaders in [[Zambia]] in 1974 until her resignation in 2007. In 1975, she fled to the [[Oshatowa refugee camp]] in Zambia, where she officially joined SWAPO. She received military training in exile before studying in the [[United Kingdom]]. In the run-up to Namibia's independence in 1989, Limbo was one of hundreds of Namibian exiles who returned to the country. She held various positions in the SWAPO-led government until her resignation in 2007 to join RDP.<ref>[http://www.newera.com.na/article.php?articleid=7329 ELECTIONS 2009: RDP's frontline quartet] New Era, 7 October 2009</ref> In September 2010, Limbo and 8 other opposition politicians were sworn-in as members of the National Assembly following a six-month boycott due to electoral irregularities in the 2009 election.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.namibian.com.na/news/full-story/archive/2010/september/article/full-house/ |title=Full house |accessdate=2012-03-31 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331214430/http://www.namibian.com.na/news/full-story/archive/2010/september/article/full-house/ |archivedate=2012-03-31 |df= }} [[The Namibian]], 15 September 2010</ref>
