{{Infobox person | name = Bob Leonard | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1941|09|16}} | birth_place = Olds, Alberta | death_date = {{Death date and age|2016|01|09|1941|09|16}} | death_place = | nationality = Canadian | other_names = | occupation = Photographer, ring announcer | years_active = 1936 – 1989, photography | known_for = Photography, writing, wrestling promoting | notable_works = }} '''Bob Leonard''' (October 16, 1941 – January 9, 2016), was a Canadian [[professional wrestling]] promoter, photographer, ring announcer, and author.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2005/04/26/1014099.html |title=Who is Bob Leonard? |date =May 18, 2005|author=Kreiser, Jamie|work=Slam! Wrestling|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2016/01/09/22591414.html |title=Goodbye and thank you, Bob Leonard |date =April 3, 2016 |author=Oliver, Greg|authorlink= Greg Oliver|work=Slam! Wrestling|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref> During his career in the professional wrestling industry he spent three decades as the perennial photographer for [[Stampede Wrestling]].
==Biography== Leonard was born in [[Olds, Alberta]] but spent most his life in [[Regina, Saskatchewan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2005/04/26/1014099.html |title=Who is Bob Leonard? |date =May 18, 2005|author=Kreiser, Jamie|work=Slam! Wrestling|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref>
Referred to by journalist [[Dave Meltzer]] as the number one pro wrestling historian of the 70s and 80s he was a multi-tasking employee of [[Stampede Wrestling]] who worked on several aspects of the promotion in backstage roles<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2005/01/09/868449.html |title=The tragic end of Freddie Sweetan |date =January 8, 2005 |author=Oliver, Greg|authorlink= |work=Slam! Wrestling|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref> and in many capacities on screen<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.f4wonline.com/daily-updates/daily-update-mike-sharpe-and-bob-leonard-pass-away-and-nakamura-205836 |title=Mike Sharpe and Bob Leonard pass away, Nakamura |date =January 18, 2016 |author=Meltzer, David|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|website=f4wonline.com|publisher=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref> but was most acknowledged for his longtime work as a photographer of matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://leaderpost.com/sports/local-sports/bob-leonard-was-reginas-mr-wrestling |title=Bob Leonard was Regina's Mr. Wrestling |date = January 29, 2016|author=Vanstone, Rob |authorlink= |publisher=[[Leader-Post]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/bs-mtblog-2008-07-transcript_of_bret_harts_hall_of_fame_speech-story.html |title=Transcript of Bret Hart's Hall of Fame speech |date =July 3, 2008 |author=Eck, Kevin |authorlink= |publisher=[[The Baltimore Sun]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.stampedewrestling.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=45&Itemid=5# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2007-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070812094649/http://www.stampedewrestling.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=45&Itemid=5# |archive-date=2007-08-12 |dead-url=no |df= }}</ref> He has been credited as having made landmark contributions toward the understanding of professional wrestling.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/2010/07/03/14598681.html |title=The history of wrestling "historians" |date =July 7, 2010 |author=KENYON, J MICHAEL|authorlink= |work=Slam! Wrestling|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Wrestling/MatMatters/2016/11/28/22686496.html |title=Saskatchewan's gifts to wrestling were Leonard and Cozman |date =November 28, 2016 |author=Oliver, Greg|authorlink= |work=Slam! Wrestling|publisher=[[Canadian Online Explorer]]|accessdate =2018-01-18}}</ref>
