'''Jean Doujat''' (1609, in [[Toulouse]] – 27 October 1688, in Paris) was a French lawyer, ''[[jurist|juris consultus]]'', professor of [[canon law]] at the [[Collège de France|Collège royal]], docteur-régent at the [[faculté de droit de Paris]], preceptor of the [[Dauphin of France|Dauphin]] and historian. His works include histories of the reign of [[Louis XIV]].

He wrote an important ''Grammaire espagnole abrégée''.<ref>[http://notices.bnf.fr/AfficherNoticeServlet?idNotice=37287109 ''Grammaire espagnole abrégée'' (1644). Texte en ligne ]</ref>

