'''Tema''', was according to the [[Bible]]<ref>[[Book of Genesis|Genesis]] 25:15</ref><ref>[[1 Chronicles]] 1:30</ref> the ninth son of [[Ishmael]]<ref>Bromiley, Geoffrey W. (1979), ''The International Standard Bible Encyclopedia'' (2nd, revised ed.), Wm. B. Eerdmans Publishing, {{ISBN|9780802837813}}</ref><ref>Rosenmüller, Ernst Friedrich Carl; Morren, Nathaniel (1841), ''The Biblical Geography of Asia Minor, Phoenicia, and Arabia'', (Thomas Clark, 1841)</ref>

The name Tema or Te'ma or  Tema' (תֵּימָא or תֵּמָא] means the [[South]]. The name is rendered Θαιμάν in [[Greek language|Greek]]  and Thema in Latin,<ref>[[Pliny the Elder|Pliny]], ''[[Natural History (Pliny)|Hist. Nat.]]'' 6:32</ref>

The name also applied to the name of the tribe that were descended from him and the [[Land of Tema|district they lived in]].<ref>[[Book of Job|Job]] 6:19</ref>

