[[File:WilhelmChristianKeilhau-OB.F06105.jpg|thumb|right|Wilhelm Keilhau]] '''Wilhelm Christian Ottesen Keilhau''' (30 July 1888 &ndash; 9 June 1954) was a Norwegian historian and economist. He was born in [[Oslo|Kristiania]]. He was appointed professor at the [[University of Oslo]] from 1934. Among his works are his thesis ''{{lang|no|Grundrentelæren}}'' from 1917 and ''{{lang|de|Die Wertungslehre}}'' from 1923. In addition to his academic career, Keilhau also engaged in other activities. He published two novels and a poetry collection. He was CEO of Norway's first airline company, [[Det Norske Luftfartrederi|Det norske Luftfartsrederi]], in 1918. During World War II he was a member of the board of directors of the London department of [[Norges Bank]].<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Wilhelm Christian Keilhau |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Wilhelm_Christian_Keilhau |language=Norwegian |accessdate=10 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Wilhelm Keilhau |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Preben |last=Munthe |authorlink=Preben Munthe |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Wilhelm_Keilhau/utdypning |language=Norwegian|accessdate=10 March 2012 }}</ref>
